SELECT researcher_name, MIN(result_data->'value') AS min_result_value, MAX(result_data->'value') AS max_result_value FROM experimental_results GROUP BY researcher_name;

SELECT COUNT(*) OVER() AS total_count, researcher_name, experiment_date FROM experimental_results;
SELECT researcher_name, DATE_PART('year', experiment_date) AS year, SUM(result_data->'value') AS total_result_value FROM experimental_results GROUP BY researcher_name, year;
SELECT AVG(DATE_PART('month', AGE(experiment_date))) AS avg_month_old_experiment FROM experimental_results;

SELECT el.log_id, er.experiment_name, lt.technician_name FROM experimental_logs el JOIN experimental_results er ON el.experiment_id = er.experiment_id JOIN lab_technicians lt ON el.technician_id = lt.technician_id;
SELECT el.log_id, el.notes FROM experimental_logs el JOIN lab_technicians lt ON el.technician_id = lt.technician_id AND lt.technician_role = 'Technician';

SELECT el.log_id, er.experiment_name, lt.technician_name, ll.lab_name FROM experimental_logs el JOIN experimental_results er ON el.experiment_id = er.experiment_id JOIN lab_technicians lt ON el.technician_id = lt.technician_id JOIN laboratories ll ON lt.lab_id = ll.lab_id;

SELECT ll.lab_name, COUNT(el.log_id) AS total_logs FROM experimental_logs el JOIN lab_technicians lt ON el.technician_id = lt.technician_id JOIN laboratories ll ON lt.lab_id = ll.lab_id GROUP BY ll.lab_name ORDER BY total_logs DESC;
SELECT er.experiment_name, AVG(el.log_id) AS avg_log_id FROM experimental_results er JOIN experimental_logs el ON er.experiment_id = el.experiment_id GROUP BY er.experiment_name;
SELECT DISTINCT technician_name, lab_name FROM lab_technicians lt JOIN laboratories ll ON lt.lab_id = ll.lab_id;
SELECT lab_name, COUNT(DISTINCT lt.technician_id) AS total_technicians FROM lab_technicians lt JOIN laboratories ll ON lt.lab_id = ll.lab_id GROUP BY lab_name;

SELECT technician_name, lab_name, COUNT(*) AS total_logs FROM lab_technicians lt JOIN experimental_logs el ON lt.technician_id = el.technician_id JOIN laboratories ll ON lt.lab_id = ll.lab_id GROUP BY technician_name, lab_name;
SELECT technician_role, COUNT(*) AS total_technicians FROM lab_technicians GROUP BY technician_role HAVING COUNT(*) > 1;

SELECT ll.lab_name, COUNT(DISTINCT er.experiment_id) AS total_experiments FROM experimental_results er JOIN lab_technicians lt ON er.experiment_id = lt.lab_id JOIN laboratories ll ON lt.lab_id = ll.lab_id GROUP BY ll.lab_name ORDER BY total_experiments DESC;
SELECT el.log_id, er.experiment_name, el.log_date - er.experiment_date AS time_difference FROM experimental_logs el JOIN experimental_results er ON el.experiment_id = er.experiment_id;

SELECT er.experiment_name, SUM(EXTRACT(DAY FROM el.log_date - er.experiment_date)) AS total_days FROM experimental_logs el JOIN experimental_results er ON el.experiment_id = er.experiment_id GROUP BY er.experiment_name;
SELECT ll.lab_location, COUNT(*) AS total_technicians FROM lab_technicians lt JOIN laboratories ll ON lt.lab_id = ll.lab_id GROUP BY ll.lab_location;

SELECT technician_name, COUNT(*) AS total_logs FROM lab_technicians lt JOIN experimental_logs el ON lt.technician_id = el.technician_id WHERE EXTRACT(MONTH FROM log_date) = 10 GROUP BY technician_name;

SELECT DISTINCT lt.technician_name, COUNT(DISTINCT el.experiment_id) AS total_experiments FROM lab_technicians lt JOIN experimental_logs el ON lt.technician_id = el.technician_id GROUP BY lt.technician_name HAVING COUNT(DISTINCT el.experiment_id) >= 2;
